<h2>What Is Methionine?</h2>
Methionine is an amino acid; the basic block that links up with other amino acids and bonds to form protein. Methionine isnâ€™t produced in the body, and it helps in the formation of cartilages. Methionine is also quite essential for many cell functions. It helps prevent hair loss and strengthens your nails.
<h2>Uses:</h2>
Methionine has other uses, apart from helping in the formation of cartilages (<a href="http://www.webmd.com/vitamins-supplements/ingredientmono-42-methionine.aspx?activeingredientid=42&amp;activeingredientname=methionine" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">2</a>). Some of them include:
